If a man divorces his wife it will create a great fuss. It will disgrace and anger his relatives, and that is the most important thing.” As one young man said, “If you want to be divorced, do it in secret!” My research showed that many men were heavily dependent on their female relatives and would be unable to survive without them.7 This dependency is not a question of lack
feminist review: issue 92 83 of money. As one man said, he would not have to work if it were not for his mother. He needed help to bring up his children. Ok, he continued, “If I don’t do the work, how will they get food to eat and pay the rent?” Another man was dependent on his wife when it came to salary payments. Living from hand to mouth, he only had enough money to get home from a long distance place of work.
Men were embarrassed about finishing a marriage that didn’t work out. For men marriage is seen as a great achievement and it is difficult to abandon it.
